headline: Costco Stock Trades at Over 50 Times Earnings for Only the 2nd Time in Its History. What Happened Last Time Could Signal What to Expect This Time.
summary: In investing lingo, one would say this business trades at 10 times its earnings or at a price-to-earnings (P/E) ratio of 10.  Buying shares of Costco Wholesale (NASDAQ: COST) at a lower P/E ratio is not possible right now.  As of this writing, Costco stock trades at 55 times its earnings, which is just the second time in its history that its P/E ratio has gone over 50.
